    "# Fundamental Image Processing Operations\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook serves as a cookbook for several fundamental image processing operations in OpenCV. Each section covers a distinct topic, demonstrating the core functions and their common use cases."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Step 1: Setup\n",
    "\n",
    "We import all necessary libraries and define the path to our shared assets folder."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import cv2\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import os\n",
    "from matplotlib import pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "# Define the relative path to the assets directory\n",
    "assets_path = os.path.join('..', '_assets')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Image Arithmetic\n",
    "\n",
    "This section covers adding two images together. We will use `cv2.add()` for simple addition and `cv2.addWeighted()` for blending.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Note:** To perform arithmetic operations, the images must be of the same size."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "img1_path = os.path.join(assets_path, 'klon.jpg')\n",
    "img2_path = os.path.join(assets_path, 'smile.jpg')\n",
    "\n",
    "img1 = cv2.imread(img1_path)\n",
    "img2 = cv2.imread(img2_path)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Resize img2 to be the same size as img1\n",
    "h, w, _ = img1.shape\n",
    "img2_resized = cv2.resize(img2, (w, h))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Simple addition (values are clipped at 255)\n",
    "simple_add = cv2.add(img1, img2_resized)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Weighted addition (blending)\n",
    "# result = α*img1 + β*img2 + γ\n",
    "weighted_add = cv2.addWeighted(img1, 0.7, img2_resized, 0.3, 0)\n",
    "\n",
    "cv2.imshow('Image 1', img1)\n",
    "cv2.imshow('Image 2 Resized', img2_resized)\n",
    "cv2.imshow('Simple Addition', simple_add)\n",
    "cv2.imshow('Weighted Addition (Blend)', weighted_add)\n",
    "cv2.waitKey(0)\n",
    "cv2.destroyAllWindows()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Color Space Conversions\n",
    "\n",
    "OpenCV can convert images between different color spaces using `cv2.cvtColor()`. The most common conversion is from BGR (OpenCV's default) to Grayscale or HSV (Hue, Saturation, Value)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "img_path = os.path.join(assets_path, 'helicopter.jpg')\n",
    "bgr_image = cv2.imread(img_path)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Convert from BGR to Grayscale\n",
    "gray_image = cv2.cvtColor(bgr_image, cv2.COLOR_BGR2GRAY)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Convert from BGR to HSV\n",
    "hsv_image = cv2.cvtColor(bgr_image, cv2.COLOR_BGR2HSV)\n",
    "\n",
    "cv2.imshow('Original BGR', bgr_image)\n",
    "cv2.imshow('Grayscale', gray_image)\n",
    "cv2.imshow('HSV', hsv_image)\n",
    "cv2.waitKey(0)\n",
    "cv2.destroyAllWindows()"
   ]
  },
